rements\nspan a range of 1 to 100 days. The photometric magnetic activity levels of\nthese stars were computed, and for 61.5% of the dwarfs, this level is similar\nto the range, from minimum to maximum, of the solar magnetic activity. We\ndemonstrate that hot dwarfs, cool dwarfs, and subgiants have very different\nrotation-age relationships, highlighting the importance of separating out\ndistinct populations when interpreting stellar rotation periods. Our sample of\ncool dwarf stars with age and metallicity data of the highest quality is\nconsistent with gyrochronology relations reported in the literature.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Mar 2014 18:05:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 12 Nov 2014 17:16:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-26"}
